            "text_hXK4Xk": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<h5>I am a slow fashion designer from Hessen, currently based in Berlin, where I completed my BA in Fashion Design at Atelier Chardon Savard in 2025.<\/h5><h5>My passion lies in the careful process of handcrafting garments that are both concept-driven and emotionally expressive. <\/h5><h5>I approach my work with the belief that responsibility can fuel creativity, given how the demands for sustainable practices are expected of designers.<\/h5><h5>Working within the traditions of haute couture and staying true to my core principles—such as working exclusively with natural fabrics and incorporating upcycling practices—I strive to make choices that reflect care, intention, and justify a long-term spot for myself in the industry.<\/h5><h5>My work has been featured at Der Berliner Salon (2025) and rewarded with the Best Craftsmanship award at Neo.Fashion (2024) —experiences that have cemented my dedication to operate through a slow fashion lens.<\/h5>",
                "width": "100%",
